In case of questions, please message TallOak.

Do 'sudo aptitude install omxplayer'.
Install webpy from pip.
Copy files in repository into /usr/omxplayerd.
create fifo pipe (mkfifo) called 'omxin'.
Create symlink 'media' to the required location (containing movies, etc) to browse.
Add '@reboot /usr/omxplayerd/omxplayerd.py >/var/log/omxplayerd.log' or similar to root crontab file.

A more verbose version of this readme is available, where more commands and explanations are given with each line. It is called "readme_verbose".
